Emberkawa Enclave[dnd-info]=The Emberkawa Enclave is an area of the Ryumon District that is somewhat separated from the rest of the district. It is enclosed by walls on all sides with two large entrances (one to the southeast and one to the southwest). The Enclave is primarily controlled by the Emberkawa Syndicate, who run casino's and other highly profitable businesses within the enclave walls.

Unique Establishments in Emberkawa Enclave[dnd-info]=The Emberkawa Enclave has many unique establishments.;*Crimson Lotus Bistro*A high-end restaurant known for its fusion cuisine that combines traditional and modern flavors. Run by a dragonborn chef named Kairo. The Crimson Lotus' specialty dish is Dragonfire Spicy Noodles. They also specialize in Ruby Fire Trout and a Cerulion Onyx Fish fish dishes.;*Golden Phoenix Tavern*A lively tavern that offers hearty meals and a wide selection of ales and spirits. It's a popular spot for locals and travelers alike. Nightly performances by local bards and entertainers.;*Sakura Blossom Sushi*A sushi restaurant that prides itself on the freshest ingredients and artistic presentation. Run by a meticulous elven chef named Aeloria. Sakura Blossom's specialty dish is the Ember Dragon Roll. Other popular dishes include the Fried Emberkawa Roll and the Sakura Roll.;*Emberkawa Grand Casino*The largest casino in the enclave, offering a variety of high-stakes games and luxurious amenities. It's a hub of activity and the centerpiece of the Emberkawa Syndicate's operations. This casino has VIP rooms for the Syndicate's most influential patrons.;*The Jade Serpent*A more intimate casino with a focus on card games and private gambling rooms. Known for its elegant décor and exclusive clientele. The Jade Serpent specializes in High-stakes poker tournaments with large prize pools.;*Fortune's Favor*A mid-sized casino known for its friendly atmosphere and variety of games, from slot machines to magical roulette and enchanted games that provide unique and magical gambling experiences.;*Flame of the Phoenix Dojo*A dojo specializing in fire-based martial arts and combat techniques, run by a tiefling master named Ignis. The dojo is known for its intense training regimen and fiery demonstrations. The dojo hosts annual fire-dance competition that attracts participants from across the district.;*Emberclaw Academy*A training school for assassins and spies, secretly operating under the guise of a martial arts dojo. Run by a shadowy figure known only as the Raven. Hidden training rooms with advanced traps and stealth challenges are common within the academy.;*The Silver Vault*A high-security vault and banking establishment where the wealthy can store their valuables and treasures. Run by a dwarven family known for their expertise in security and protection. The dwarves implement many magical defenses and traps to deter theft.;*Ebon Mirror Emporium*A shop specializing in magical mirrors and enchanted items, run by a mysterious tiefling named Mirage. The shop is known for its rare and unique inventory. Mirage regularly procures artifacts and magic items for various Syndicate members.;*Midnight Lotus*An exclusive nightclub offering exotic drinks and private lounges. It's a popular spot for the enclave's elite to unwind and socialize. The midnight Lotus offers performances by exotic dancers and illusionists.;*Whispering Ember Apothecary*A high-end apothecary offering rare potions and alchemical supplies. Run by a knowledgeable human alchemist named Selene. The apothecary offers many potions that offer temporary enhancements and unique effects.;*Obsidian Forge*A blacksmith shop known for crafting custom weapons and armor for the Syndicate's enforcers. Run by a half-orc named Grond. Grond offers many enchanted weaponry with unique properties.;*The Hidden Lotus*A secretive gambling den and opium house, accessible only through hidden entrances and known only to a select few. This is often visited for its private rooms for discreet transactions and meetings.;*Emberkawa Market*A bustling market where vendors sell a variety of goods, from exotic foods to magical trinkets. It's a hub of commerce and trade within the enclave. The market hosts night market events with special performances and rare goods.;*Dragon’s Breath Inn*A luxurious inn catering to wealthy travelers and Syndicate members. Known for its opulent rooms and excellent service. The inn features hidden passageways that connect to various parts of the enclave for discreet movement.;*Shadow’s Edge Theater*A grand theater offering plays, musicals, and other performances. It's a cultural center within the enclave. The theature has occasional underground performances that feature controversial and provocative themes.;These establishments reflect the unique blend of culture, commerce, and clandestine activities that define the Emberkawa Enclave within the Ryumon District.
